        <description>

The Mariner 5 Triaxial Low Field Helium Magnetometer measured
interplanetary and Venusian magnetic fields by detecting changes in
helium absorptivity to circularly polarized infrared light. Mounted on a
1.5-m boom, it had a plus/minus 204 nT range with 0.2 nT precision. It
operated in high-rate mode (3 samples/12.6s) from June-July 1967 and
low-rate mode (3 samples/50.4s) for the remaining mission. Data quality
was excellent except for a brief uncertain period in September-October
1967.

        </description>
